Left over from the Age of the Magi, when mages were plentiful, these robes are sturdy, but fairly common. They last a long time, rarely wearing out.
This helm mounts two special crystal lenses over the wearer's eyes that grant a +5 bonus to Spot checks.

Forged by clerics of Suhili, the sun goddess, these shields are constantly aglow with the golden fires of the sun. Depending on the skill and intent of the crafter, some Shields of the Sun carry more potent powers as well.

This simple rope belt, when wrapped around a person's waist, confers increased ability in unarmed combat.  

When the Shining Moon order of monks were attacked by a rival order, it was necessary for some of the apprentices to rise more rapidly than they normally could. These belts allowed the younger monks to defend their order with great speed and skill.

Blessed by priests of Calahi the god of merchants and travel, these boots seem to make even the most arduous journey easier and more pleasant. This is accomplished not by increasing the wearer's speed, but by making him hardier and more resistant to pain. Numerous versions of these boots exist, their power varying largely in accordance with the priest who blessed them.
Monks who are followers of Suhili know that nothing is a persistant or dangerous as the sun. These boots a rewarded to those who master different techniques within the Rising Sun Order.
Relics from the Age of the Magi, these bracers can still be found in the common gear of most adventurers. Anything that makes an adventurer quicker and harder to hit is a must-have item.

Borderland guards have traditionally donned these cloaks while on duty. In recent years the borderlands have become more dangerous, and fewer soldiers are willing to enter the northern reaches of Valratha.

Also referred to as the Disciples of the Saint Sollars, the Monastic Order of the Yellow Rose is known equally for its acts of great loyalty to its allies and those of great destruction to its enemies. Monks of this Order frequently travel alongside paladins of Jaess, serving as trusted guides and companions to these knights of the servant lord.
